question: What are the eligibilities for applying for student travel award
answer: To apply for the IJCAI Travel and Accessibility Grant Program, due to limited funds, applicants are required to seek support from their respective departments or local AI societies prior to applying for this grant. After the conference, in order to receive the grant, a post-conference report and receipts totaling the grant amount must be provided. In the event that the applications for the travel grant exceed the available funds, preference will be given firstly to students and other applicants who have a technical paper accepted, and then to students and other applicants who are actively participating in the conference in some manner.
from: IJCAI 2023/grants/IJCAI-AIJ 2023 Travel and Accessibility Grant Program

question: What are the eligibility criteria for students wishing to participate in the IJCAI Student Volunteer Program?
answer: Any full-time university student, at any level, may apply to participate, whether or not they are presenting a paper. However, priority will be given to those students who have accepted contribution to the IJCAI including main conference, workshop, tutorial, competition and so on.

question: What is the primary focus of the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track at IJCAI 2023?
answer: This special track is dedicated to research triggered by real-world key questions, is carried out in collaboration with civil society stakeholders, and uses AI to work towards the SDGs and LNOB.

question: What are the requirements for submitting research papers to the "Multi-Year Track on AI and Social Good" special track?
answer: Research papers should have the same format (7 pages + 2 pages for references) and follow the same general instructions as for the main conference (seehttps://ijcai-23.org/call-for-papers/). Also, just as the research papers submitted to the main track of IJCAI 2023, papers in this track should beanonymous.
from: IJCAI 2023/calls/Call For Papers And Projects: Multi-Year Track On AI And Social Good (Special Track)/5/Submission of Research Papers

question: What are the requirements for submitting research papers to the "AI The Arts And Creativity" special track?
answer: Research paper submissions must meet all the Submission Requirements described in the above general instructions. In particular, they must be anonymous, and papers are expected to satisfy the highest scientific standards as submissions to the main track of IJCAI 2023. Also, double submissions to the special track and main conference are not allowed.
